{"title_page": "Macclesfield District General Hospital", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox hospital\n| Name        = Macclesfield District General Hospital\n| Org/Group   = [[East Cheshire NHS Trust]]\n| Image       = Pool at Macclesfield General Hospital - geograph.org.uk - 219127.jpg\n| Caption     = Macclesfield District General Hospital\n| map_type    = Cheshire\n| map_caption = Shown in Cheshire\n| latitude    = <!-- used only for adding a map, with map_type -->\n| longitude   = <!-- used only for adding a map, with map_type -->\n| Logo        = <!-- optional -->\n| Location    = [[Macclesfield]]\n| State       = <!-- optional -->\n| Region      = [[Cheshire]]\n| Country     = England\n| Coordinates = {{Coord|53.2624|N|2.1419|W|type:landmark_region:GB-WRL|display=inline,title}}\n| HealthCare  = NHS\n| Type        = General\n| Speciality  = <!-- optional -->\n| Standards   = <!-- optional if no national standards -->\n| Emergency   = \n| Affiliation = \n| Beds        = <!-- optional -->\n| Founded     = 1844\n| Closed      = <!-- optional -->\n| Website     = {{URL|http://www.eastcheshire.nhs.uk/}}\n| Wiki-Links  = <!-- optional -->\n}}\n'''Macclesfield District General Hospital''' is a health facility in [[Macclesfield]], [[Cheshire]]. It is managed by the [[East Cheshire NHS Trust]].\n\n==History==\nThe hospital has its origins in the Macclesfield Workhouse and Hospital which opened at West Park in 1844.<ref name=workhouses>{{cite web|url=http://www.workhouses.org.uk/Macclesfield/|title=Macclesfield|publisher=Workhouses|accessdate=9 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=na>{{cite web|url=http://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/hospitalrecords/details.asp?id=1056&page=35|title=Macclesfield District General Hospital, West Park and Infirmary, Macclesfield|publisher=National Archives|accessdate=9 December 2018}}</ref> A fever hospital was completed in 1854 and a new hospital block was completed in 1881.<ref name=workhouses/> It became West Park Hospital in 1930 and joined the [[National Health Service]] as Macclesfield Hospital, West Park Branch in 1948.<ref name=na/>\n\nMeanwhile the Macclesfield Infirmary, which had been built at Cumberland Street in 1868,<ref name=hansard>{{cite web|url=https://api.parliament.uk/historic-hansard/commons/1974/nov/15/hospitals-macclesfield|title=Hospitals (Macclesfield)|date=15 November 1974|publisher=Hansard|accessdate=9 December 2018}}</ref> evolved to join the National Health Service as Macclesfield Hospital, Infirmary Branch in 1948.<ref name=infirm>{{cite web|url=http://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/hospitalrecords/details.asp?id=1057|title=Macclesfield District General Hospital, Infirmary Branch, Macclesfield|publisher=National Archives|accessdate=9 December 2018}}</ref> The Infirmary Branch moved to Prestbury Road in 1980.<ref name=infirm/>\n\nThe operation of the hospital became very inefficient as clinical operations were split between the West Park Branch and the Infirmary Branch.<ref name=hansard/> Accordingly the hospital was re-built as Macclesfield District General Hospital at West Park in the early 1980s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eastcheshire.nhs.uk/About-The-Trust/Aboutthetrust.htm|title=About the Trust|publisher=East Cheshire NHS Trust|accessdate=9 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe [[sustainability and transformation plan]] for Merseyside and Cheshire proposed to downgrade the emergency department at Macclesfield District General Hospital to a minor injuries and illnesses unit,<ref>{{cite news|title=Leaked STP document reveals A&E downgrade plans|url=https://www.hsj.co.uk/newsletter/sectors/acute-care/leaked-stp-document-reveals-ae-downgrade-plans/7013035.article|accessdate=4 November 2016|publisher=Health Service Journal|date=3 November 2016}}</ref> but within a fortnight, after widespread opposition it was altered to read \"\u201cThe clear view is that the best model of care will include an A&E department at Macclesfield staffed by hospital doctors and clinicians.\u201d<ref>{{cite news|title=Cheshire backtracks on potential A&E downgrade|url=https://www.hsj.co.uk/hsj-local/providers/east-cheshire-nhs-trust/cheshire-backtracks-on-potential-ae-downgrade/7013771.article|accessdate=25 January 2017|publisher=Health Service Journal|date=1 December 2016}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Cheshire}}\n*{{Official site|http://www.eastcheshire.nhs.uk/}}\n\n[[Category:Hospitals in Cheshire]]\n[[Category:NHS hospitals in England]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox hospital\n| Name        = Macclesfield District General Hospital\n| Org/Group   = [[East Cheshire NHS Trust]]\n| Image       = Pool at Macclesfield General Hospital - geograph.org.uk - 219127.jpg\n| Caption     = Macclesfield District General Hospital\n| map_type    = Cheshire\n| map_caption = Shown in Cheshire\n| latitude    = <!-- used only for adding a map, with map_type -->\n| longitude   = <!-- used only for adding a map, with map_type -->\n| Logo        = <!-- optional -->\n| Location    = [[Macclesfield]]\n| State       = <!-- optional -->\n| Region      = [[Cheshire]]\n| Country     = England\n| Coordinates = {{Coord|53.2624|N|2.1419|W|type:landmark_region:GB-WRL|display=inline,title}}\n| HealthCare  = NHS\n| Type        = General\n| Speciality  = <!-- optional -->\n| Standards   = <!-- optional if no national standards -->\n| Emergency   = \n| Affiliation = \n| Beds        = <!-- optional -->\n| Founded     = 1844\n| Closed      = <!-- optional -->\n| Website     = {{URL|http://www.eastcheshire.nhs.uk/}}\n| Wiki-Links  = <!-- optional -->\n}}\n'''Macclesfield District General Hospital''' is a health facility in [[Macclesfield]], [[Cheshire]]. It is managed by the [[East Cheshire NHS Trust]].\n\n==History==\nThe hospital has its origins in the Macclesfield Workhouse and Hospital which opened at West Park in 1844.<ref name=workhouses>{{cite web|url=http://www.workhouses.org.uk/Macclesfield/|title=Macclesfield|publisher=Workhouses|accessdate=9 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=na>{{cite web|url=http://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/hospitalrecords/details.asp?id=1056&page=35|title=Macclesfield District General Hospital, West Park and Infirmary, Macclesfield|publisher=National Archives|accessdate=9 December 2018}}</ref> A fever hospital was completed in 1854 and a new hospital block was completed in 1881.<ref name=workhouses/> It became West Park Hospital in 1930 and joined the [[National Health Service]] as Macclesfield Hospital, West Park Branch in 1948.<ref name=na/>\n\nMeanwhile the Macclesfield Infirmary, which had been built at Cumberland Street in 1868,<ref name=hansard>{{cite web|url=https://api.parliament.uk/historic-hansard/commons/1974/nov/15/hospitals-macclesfield|title=Hospitals (Macclesfield)|date=15 November 1974|publisher=Hansard|accessdate=9 December 2018}}</ref> evolved to join the National Health Service as Macclesfield Hospital, Infirmary Branch in 1948.<ref name=infirm>{{cite web|url=http://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/hospitalrecords/details.asp?id=1057|title=Macclesfield District General Hospital, Infirmary Branch, Macclesfield|publisher=National Archives|accessdate=9 December 2018}}</ref> The Infirmary Branch moved to Prestbury Road in 1980.<ref name=infirm/>\n\nThe operation of the hospital became very inefficient as clinical operations were split between the West Park Branch and the Infirmary Branch.<ref name=hansard/> Accordingly the hospital was re-built as Macclesfield District General Hospital at West Park in the early 1980s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eastcheshire.nhs.uk/About-The-Trust/Aboutthetrust.htm|title=About the Trust|publisher=East Cheshire NHS Trust|accessdate=9 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe [[sustainability and transformation plan]] for Merseyside and Cheshire proposed to downgrade the emergency department at Macclesfield District General Hospital to a minor injuries and illnesses unit,<ref>{{cite news|title=Leaked STP document reveals A&E downgrade plans|url=https://www.hsj.co.uk/newsletter/sectors/acute-care/leaked-stp-document-reveals-ae-downgrade-plans/7013035.article|accessdate=4 November 2016|publisher=Health Service Journal|date=3 November 2016}}</ref> but within a fortnight, after widespread opposition it was altered to read \"\u201cThe clear view is that the best model of care will include an A&E department at Macclesfield staffed by hospital doctors and clinicians.\u201d<ref>{{cite news|title=Cheshire backtracks on potential A&E downgrade|url=https://www.hsj.co.uk/hsj-local/providers/east-cheshire-nhs-trust/cheshire-backtracks-on-potential-ae-downgrade/7013771.article|accessdate=25 January 2017|publisher=Health Service Journal|date=1 December 2016}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official site|http://www.eastcheshire.nhs.uk/}}\n\n[[Category:Hospitals in Cheshire]]\n[[Category:NHS hospitals in England]]\n", "name_user": "Espresso Addict", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:+portal", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Macclesfield_District_General_Hospital"}
